Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
viewSnapshot(25.10)                                        viewSnapshot(25.10)

Name
       viewSnapshot  -  Opens a window SnapShot Result for viewing saved snap-
       shots

Syntax
       viewSnapshot

       [-help]

       -dir <string>

       [-name <string>]

       [-view <string>]

       Opens a window SnapShot Result for viewing saved  snapshots.  Snapshots
       are  selected based on the options: -dir and -name. The window displays
       design views controlled by the -view option and also shows QoR  parame-
       ters  (WNS,TNS, Placement Overlap, and congestion) saved at the time of
       creating the snapshot.

Parameters
       -dir <string>
              Specifies the directory of the saved snapshot, when opted  alone
              it will show all snapshots saved in the directory.

       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each viewSnapshot parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command: man viewSnapshot.

       -name <string>
              Specifies the name of snapshot to be viewed in the SnapShot  Re-
              sult window.

       -view <string>
              Specifies the view of the design you want to see in SnapShot Re-
              sult  window.  You  can see multiple views by listing them under
              this option.

              Default: The fplan view is shown in the SnapShot Result window.

       Note: This command will not work in the -nowin mode.

Examples
              * The following command will show all the snapshots  present  in
                the  directory  /work/user1<,>  along  with all QoR parameters
                (WNS, TNS, Placement Overlap, and Congestion). By default only
                the fplan view will be displayed.

                viewSnapshot -dir {/work/user1}

              * The following command will show snapshots with  the  name  cts
                along  with  all  QoR parameters (WNS, TNS, Placement Overlap,
                and Congestion). By default only the fplan view will  be  dis-
                played.

                viewSnapshot -dir {/work/user1} -name cts

              * The  following  command  will show snapshots with the name cts
                along with all QoR parameters (WNS,  TNS,  Placement  Overlap,
                and  Congestion).  Only design views ctswill be shown as opted
                under the -view option.

                viewSnapshot -dir {/work/user1} -name cts -view cts

              * The following command will show all the snapshots  present  in
                the  directory  /work/user1along with all QoR parameters (WNS,
                TNS, Placement Overlap, and Congestion). All the views will be
                shown side by side.

                viewSnapshot -dir {/work/user1} -view {fplan amoeba place}

